"The user starts exploring View 1 at the overview level to identify the overall distribution of water consumption and yield among irrigation methods using scatter plots. The user uses brushing interactions to select specific ranges of interest, which updates View 2 (exploration level) to display box plots grouped by irrigation method and districts, enabling outlier detection. From there, the user drills down into View 3 (detail level), where heatmaps provide spatial analysis of water usage efficiency across districts and crop types, refined with hover interactions for precise insights. Finally, the user moves to View 4 (insight level) to analyze anomalies using bar charts sorted by efficiency and toggles between aggregate and detailed views."